As I reflect on everything that's happened this year, I am still processing this trip to Paris that closed out my year.

I struggled so hard to find my footing for so much of 2022 but the last few months I've let go of trying to control everything and have embraced the flow of life - and it's been such a cathartic release that has eased my anxiety and brought so many amazing people and opportunities to me.

Thank you to the Chanel team for this amazing trip.

A little over a week ago I moved into my own space in Brooklyn. Never thought I’d return to New York but couldn’t be happier to be back and have this place to call home. 

When I left the city over a year and a half ago, I had so many thoughts, plans and ideas of what I thought my life would look and slowly realized that once I was living that reality it wasn’t actually making me happy.

So in September I got rid of my apartment in California, sold most of my things and lived out of a suitcase for nearly 4 months. I quickly realized that when I was letting my intuition guide me instead of holding onto what I thought my life should look like, I felt more free than I have in a long time. 

I feel so grateful to have all of these experiences, to be here now and can’t wait to share more as I get settled into my new home.

When I was 13 I saved a photo of this little island in Greece and dreamed about one day being able to visit. Then as the years went on and I learned more about the world of design, I also added Denmark to my list of places I one day wanted to see. 

More than a decade later, I finally saved enough and took this summer off to visit these places.

The trip was deeply healing in many ways and felt like the culmination of lifelong dreams that I never thought would happen so quickly. 

Though my film camera died half way through the trip and half of the film got ruined on the journey home— these are some photos that I was able to salvage that hopefully capture the essence of places that now hold a special place in my soul.

For @sandroparis FW’23 

Shot by @theochoi_
